# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Appendix (HPC offload): lattice thermal conductivity of crystalline germanium
# by reverse non-equilibrium MD (Mueller-Plathe momentum swap), for a classical
# (Tersoff) and a machine-learned (SNAP) potential.
#
# This is the same method as Tutorial 8 (silicon) but set up for a more powerful
# machine: larger cells, longer runs, and an MPI domain decomposition along the
# long (z) axis.  The SNAP runs are ~100x more expensive than Tersoff and are
# meant to be run on many cores.  NOT an interactive tutorial input.
#
# Parameters are passed on the command line, e.g.
#   mpirun -np 256 lmp -in kappa_ge.lmp -v tag tersoff -v pot pot_ge_tersoff.mod \
#                      -v a0 5.658 -v ncross 6 -v nz 40 80 120 160 200
#   mpirun -np 512 lmp -in kappa_ge.lmp -v tag snap    -v pot pot_ge_snap.mod \
#                      -v a0 5.760 -v ncross 6 -v nz 20 40 60 80
# Each length writes one record to kappa_${tag}.yaml and a temperature profile
# profile_${tag}_${nz}.dat; analyze both potentials together with plot_ge.py.

variable swap  equal 100                 # momentum swap every 100 steps (0.1 ps)

print "# finite-size RNEMD thermal conductivity of germanium (${tag})"     file kappa_${tag}.yaml screen no
print "# finite-size RNEMD thermal conductivity of germanium (${tag})"     file kappa_snap.yaml screen no
print "# records: ncells length_A edelta_eV time_ps area_A2 (heat along z, 20 slabs)"     append kappa_${tag}.yaml screen no
print "# records: ncells length_A edelta_eV time_ps area_A2 (heat along z, 20 slabs)"     append kappa_snap.yaml screen no

label loop
clear
  using 1 OpenMP thread(s) per MPI task
units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p
lattice diamond ${a0}
lattice diamond 5.760
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 5.76 5.76 5.76
region box block 0 ${ncross} 0 ${ncross} 0 ${nz}
region box block 0 6 0 ${ncross} 0 ${nz}
region box block 0 6 0 6 0 ${nz}
region box block 0 6 0 6 0 20
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (34.56 34.56 115.2)
  2 by 4 by 8 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 5760 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (34.56 34.56 115.2)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.061 seconds
mass 1 72.63
include ${pot}
include pot_ge_snap.mod
pair_style snap
pair_coeff * * Ge_Zuo_JPCA2020.snapcoeff Ge_Zuo_JPCA2020.snapparam Ge
Reading potential file Ge_Zuo_JPCA2020.snapcoeff with DATE: 2020-01-31
SNAP Element = Ge, Radius 0.5, Weight 1
Reading potential file Ge_Zuo_JPCA2020.snapparam with DATE: 2020-01-31
SNAP keyword rcutfac 5.5
SNAP keyword twojmax 8
SNAP keyword rfac0 0.99363
SNAP keyword rmin0 0
SNAP keyword quadraticflag 0
SNAP keyword bzeroflag 0
velocity all create 300.0 4928459 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
timestep 0.001

# 1) relax the box to its 300 K equilibrium size (each potential has its own a0)
fix npt all npt temp 300.0 300.0 0.1 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
thermo 20000
run 30000
